value.value: Human GPX1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 3p21.3 and is approximately 12 kb in length. This allele, which encodes glutathione peroxidase 1 protein, is involved in detoxification of hydrogen peroxide. Variant alleles of GPX1 are associated with type 2 diabetes mellitus as well as certain types of cancer such as breast, lung and prostate cancer.
